Japanese non epigamic specimens (fide 
Imajima, 1966
), with antennae, dorsum and dorsal cirri dark red; with ciliary bands across dorsum, nuchal ridges present; lacking occipital flap. Dorsal cirri alternating in length, shorter than body width, and ventral simple chaetae on posterior parapodia, unidentate, slightly hooked, with short, fine spines on margin.

